headline.main: NAVY SEES JAPAN SHUNNING SEA TEST; Delaying Actions Expected as Result -- Tarawa Lessons Are Closely Studied

lead_paragraph: PEARL HARBOR, Nov. 30 -- Japan may now be expected to remain on the defensive along her harassed eastern flank, cautiously holding on to her powerful navy and fighting delaying actions wherever we attack, it was stated here today.
abstract: Jap Navy believed planning to fight only delaying actions
